cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.SY 

The paper deals with pedestrian behaviour recognition using machine learning models, specifically deep learning and statistical models. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the problem of detecting hazardous pedestrian behaviour is relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the time-critical aspect of the problem makes it relevant to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
